\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 I DID NOT KNOW whether we should turn north or south.
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Somewhere to the north lay the Ascian army, and it was
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 possible that if we came too near the lines we would be
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 c\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 aught up in some swift maneuver. Yet the farther south we
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 went, the less likely we were to find anyone who would help
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 us, and the more probable it became that we would be arrested 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 as deserters. In the end I turned northward; no doubt
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 I acted largely from \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 habit, and I am still not sure if I did well
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 or ill.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 The dew had already dried upon the road, and it\hich\f2 \rquote \loch\f2 s dusty
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 surface showed no footprints. To either side, for three paces
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 or more, the vegetation was a uniform grey. We soon passed
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 out of the forest. The r\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 oad wound down a hill and over a
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 bridge that vaulted a small river at the bottom of a rock-
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 strewn valley.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 We left it there and went down to the water to drink and
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 bathe our faces. I had not shaved since I had turned my back
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 on Lake Diuturna, and though \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 I had noticed none when I
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 took the flint and striker from the soldier's pocket, I ventured
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 to ask him if he carried a razor.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 I mention this trifling incident because it was the first
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 thing I said to him that he seemed to comprehend. He
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 nodded, then reach\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 ing under his hauberk produced one of
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 those little blades that country people use, razors their
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 smiths grind from the halves of worn oxshoes. I touched it
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 up on the broken whetstone I still carried and stropped it on
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 the leg of my boot, then asked if he ha\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 d soap. If he did, he
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 failed to understand me, and after a moment he seated him-
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 self on a rock from which he could stare into the water, re-
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 minding me very much of Dorcas. I longed to question him
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 about the fields of Death, to learn all that he remembere\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 d of
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 that time that is, perhaps, dark only to us. Instead, I washed
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 my face in the cold river water and scraped my cheeks and
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 chin as well as I could. When I sheathed his razor and tried
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 to return it to him, he did not seem to know what to do with
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 it, so I\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2  kept it.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 For most of the rest of that day we walked. Several times
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 we were stopped and questioned; more often we stopped
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 others and questioned them. Gradually I developed an elaborate 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 lie: I was the lictor of a civil judge who accompanied the
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Autarch; \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 we had encountered this soldier on the road, and
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 my master had ordered me to see that he was cared for; he
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 could not speak, and so I did not know what unit he was
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 from. That last was true enough.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 We crossed other roads and sometimes followed them.
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Twice \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 we reached great camps where tens of thousands of
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 soldiers lived in cities of tents. At each, those who tended the
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 sick told me that though they would have bandaged my companion's 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 wounds had he been bleeding, they could not take
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 responsibility for him as \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 he was. By the time I spoke to the
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 second, I no longer asked the location of the Pelerines but
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 only to be directed to a place where we might find shelter. It
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 was nearly night.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "There is a lazaret three leagues from here that may take
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 you in." My informan\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 t looked from one of us to the other,
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 and seemed to have almost as much sympathy for me as for
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 the soldier, who stood mute and dazed. "Co west and north
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 until you see a road to the tight that passes between two big
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 trees. It is about half as wide as the on\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 e you will have been
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 following. Go down that. Are you armed?"
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 I shook my head; I had put the soldier's falchion back in
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 his scabbard. "I was forced to leave my sword behind with my
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 master's servants\hich\f2 \emdash \loch\f2 I couldn't have carried it and managed this
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 man too."
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "Then you must beware of beasts. It would be better if
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 you had something that would shoot, but I can't give you
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 anything."
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 I fumed to go, but he stopped me with a hand on my
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 shoulder.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "Leave him if you're attacked," he said. "And if you're
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 forced to l\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 eave him, don't feel too badly about it. I've seen
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 cases like his before. He's not likely to recover."
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "He has already recovered," I told him.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Although this man would not allow us to stay or lend me a
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 weapon, he did provide us with something to eat; an\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 d I departed 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 with more cheerfulness than I had felt for some time.
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 We were in a valley where the western hills had risen to
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 obscure the sun a watch or more before. As I walked along
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 beside the soldier, I discovered that it was no longer necessary 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 for me \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 to hold his arm. I could release it, and he continued 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 to walk at my side like any friend. His face was not
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 really like Jonas's, which had been long and narrow, but once
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 when I saw it sidelong I caught something there so reminiscent 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 of Jonas that I felt a\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 lmost that I had seen a ghost.
\par 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 The grey road was greenish-white in the moonlight; the
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 trees and brush to either side looked black. As we strode
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 along I began to talk. Partially, I admit, it was from sheer
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 loneliness; yet I had other reasons as well. Unque\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 stionably
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 there are beasts, like the alzabo, who attack men as foxes do
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 fowls, but I have been told that there are many others who
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 will flee if they are warned in time of human presence. Then
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 too, I thought that if I spoke to the soldier as I might have to
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 any other man, any ill-intentioned persons who heard us
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 would be less apt to guess how unlikely he was to resist them.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "Do you recall last night?" I began. "You slept very
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 heavily."
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 There was no reply.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "Perhaps I never told you this, but I have the fa\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 cility of
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 recalling everything. I can't always lay hands on it when I
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 want, but it is always there; some memories, you know, are
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 like escaped clients wandering through the oubliette. One
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 may not be able to produce them on demand, but they are
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 always there,\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2  they cannot get away.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "Although, come to think of it, that isn't entirely true.
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 The fourth and lowest level of our oubliette has been abandoned
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 there are never enough clients to fill the topmost
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 three anyway, and perhaps eventually Master Gurloes will
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 g\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 ive up the third. We only keep it open now for the mad
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 ones that no official ever comes to see. If they were in one of
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 the higher levels, their noise would disturb the others. Not
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 all of them are noisy, of course. Some are as quiet as
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 yourself."
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Again th\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 ere was no reply. In the moonlight I could not tell
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 if be was paying attention to me, but remembering the razor
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 I persevered.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "I went that way myself once. Through the fourth level, I
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 mean. I used to have a dog, and I kept him there, but he ran
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 away. I w\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 ent after him and found a tunnel that left our
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 oubliette. Eventually I crawled out of a broken pedestal in a
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 place called the Atrium of Time. It was full of sundials. I
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 met a young woman there who was really more beautiful
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 than anyone I've ever seen since\hich\f2 \emdash \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 more lovely even than
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Jolenta, I think, though not in the same way."
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 The soldier said nothing, yet now something told me he
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 heard me; perhaps it was no more than a slight movement of
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 his head seen from a corner of my eye.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "Her name was Valeria, and I t\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 hink she was younger than
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 I, although she seemed older. She had dark, curling hair, like
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Thecla's, but her eyes were dark too. Thecla's were violet.
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 She had the finest skin I have ever seen, like rich milk mixed
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 with the juice of pomegranates and strawberr\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 ies.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "But I didn't set out to talk about Valeria, but about
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Dorcas. Dorcas is lovely too, though she is very thin, almost
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 like a child. Her face is a peri's, and her complexion is flecked
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 with freckles like bits of gold. Her hair was long before she
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 cut \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 it; she always wore flowers there."
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 I paused again. I had continued to talk of women because
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 that seemed to have caught his attention^ Now I could not
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 say if he were still listening or not.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "Before I left Thrax I went to see Dorcas. It was in her
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 room,\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2  in an inn called the Duck's Nest. She was in bed and
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 naked, but she kept the sheet over herself, just as if we had
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 never slept together\hich\f2 \emdash \loch\f2 we who had walked and ridden so far,
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 camping in places where no voice had been heard since the
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 land was called up from \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 the sea, and climbing hills where no
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 feet had ever walked but the sun's. She was leaving me and I
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 her, and neither of us really wished it otherwise, though at
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 the last she was afraid and asked me to come with her after
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 all.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "She said she thought the Claw\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2  had the same power over
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 time that Father Inire's mirrors are said to have over distance. 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 I didn't think much of the remark then\hich\f2 \emdash \loch\f2 I'm not really
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 a very intelligent man, I suppose, not a philosopher at ail-
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 but now I find it interesting. She told me, 'When \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 you
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 brought the uhlan back to life it was because the Claw
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 twisted time for him to the point at which he still lived.
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 When you half-healed your friend's wounds, it was because it
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 bent the moment to one when they would be nearly healed.'
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Don't you think tha\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 t's interesting? A little while after I
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 pricked your forehead with the Claw, you made a strange
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 sound. I think it may have been your death rattle."
\par 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 I waited. The soldier did not speak, but quite unexpectedly 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 I felt his hand on my shoulder. I had been tal\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 king
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 almost flippantly; his touch brought home to me the seriousness 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 of what I had been saying. If it were true\hich\f2 \emdash \loch\f2 or even
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 some trifling approximation to the truth\hich\f2 \emdash \loch\f2 then I had toyed
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 with powers I understood no better than Casdoe's son, whom
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 I had tried to mak\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 e my own, would have understood the
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 giant ring that took his life.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "No wonder then that you're dazed. It must be a terrible
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 thing to move backward in time, and still more terrible to
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 pass backward through death. I was about to say that it
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 would be like b\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 eing born again; but it would be much worse
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 than that, I think, because an infant lives already in his
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 mother's womb." I hesitated. "I... Thecia, I mean ... never
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 bore a child."
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Perhaps only because I had been thinking of his confusion,
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 I found I was con\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 fused myself, so that I scarcely knew who I
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 was. At last I said lamely, "You must excuse me. When I'm
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 tired, and sometimes when I'm near sleep, I come near to
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 becoming someone else." (For whatever reason, his grip on
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 my shoulder tightened when I said that.\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 ) "It's a long story
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 that has nothing to do with you. I wanted to say that in the
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Atrium of Time, the breaking of the pedestal had tilted the
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 dials so their gnomons no longer pointed true, and I have
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 heard that when that happens, the watches of day stop, o\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 r
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 run backward for some part of each day. You carry a pocket
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 dial, so you know that for it to tell time truly you must direct
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 its gnomon toward the sun. The sun remains stationary while
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Urth dances about him, and it is by her dancing that we
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 know the time,\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2  just as a deaf man might still beat out the
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 rhythm of a tarantella by observing the swaying of the dancers. 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 But what if the sun himself were to dance? Then, too,
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 the march of the moments might become a retreat.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "I don't know if you believe in the New S\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 un\hich\f2 \emdash \loch\f2 I'm not sure
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 I ever have. But if he will exist, he will be the Conciliator
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 come again, and thus Conciliator and New Sun are only two
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 names for the same individual, and we may ask why that
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 individual should be called the New Sun. What do you
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 think? Might\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2  it not be for this power to move time?"
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Now I felt indeed that time itself had stopped. Around us
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 the trees rose dark and silent; night had freshened the air. I
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Could think of nothing more to say, and I was ashamed to
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 talk nonsense, because I felt someh\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 ow that the soldier had
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 been listening attentively to all I had said. Before us I saw
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 two pines far thicker through their trunks than the others
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 lining the road, and a pale path of white and green that
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 threaded its way between them. "There!" I exclaimed.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 But when we reached them, I had to halt the soldier with
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 my hands and turn him by the shoulders before he followed
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 me. I noticed a dark splatter in the dust and bent to touch it.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 It was clotted blood. "We are on the right road," I told
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 him. "They have b\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 een bringing the wounded here."
\par 
\par 
\par 
\par }{\b\fs24\dbch\af23 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 IV
\par 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Fever}{\dbch\af23 
\par 
\par 
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 I CANNOT SAY how far we walked, or how far worn the night
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 was before we reached our destination. I know that I began
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 to stumble some time after we turned aside from the main
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 road, and that it became a sort \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 of disease to me; just as some
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 sick men cannot stop coughing and others cannot keep their
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 hands from shaking, so I tripped, and a few steps farther on
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 tripped again, and then again. Unless I thought of nothing
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 else, the toe of my left boot caught at my rig\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 ht heel, and I
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 could not concentrate my mind\hich\f2 \emdash \loch\f2 my thoughts ran off with
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 every step I took.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Fireflies glimmered in the trees to either side of the path,
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 and for a long time I supposed that the lights ahead of us
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 were only more such insects and did not hurry\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2  my pace.
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Then, very suddenly as it seemed to me, we were beneath
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 some shadowy roof where men and women with yellow lamps
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 moved up and down between long rows of shrouded cots. A
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 woman in clothes I supposed were black took charge of us
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 and led us to another\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2  place where there were chairs of leather
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 and horn, and a fire burned in a brazier. There I saw that her
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 gown was scarlet, and she wore a scarlet hood, and for a
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 .moment I thought that she was Cyriaca.
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "Your friend is very ill, isn't he?" she said. "Do yo\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 u know
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 what is the matter with him?"
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 And the soldier shook his head and answered, "No. I'm
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 not even sure who he is."
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 I was too stunned to speak. She took my hand, then re-
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 leased it and took the soldier's. "He has a fever. So do you.
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Now that the heat \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 of summer is come, we see more disease
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 each day. You should have boiled your water and kept your-
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 selves as clean of lice as you could."
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 She turned to me. "You have a great many shallow cuts
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 too, and some them are infected. Rock shards?"
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 I managed to s\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 ay, "I'm not the one who is ill. I brought my
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 friend here."
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "You are both ill, and I suspect you brought each other. I
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 doubt that either of you would have reached us without the
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 other. Was it rock shards? Some weapon of the enemy's?"
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "Rock shards, yes.\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2  A weapon of a friend's."
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "That is the worst thing, I am told\hich\f2 \emdash \loch\f2 to be fired upon by
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 your own side. But the fever is the chief concern." She hesitated, 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 looking from the soldier to me and back. "I'd like to
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 put you both in bed now, but you'll have to go to \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 the bath
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 first,"
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 She clapped her hands to summon a burly man with a
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 shaven head. He took our arms and began to lead us away,
