\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "ONCE NOT VERY long ago and not very far from the place
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 where I was born, there was a fine farm. It was especially
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 noted for its poultry: flocks of ducks white as snow, ge\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 ese
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 nearly as large as swans and so fat they could scarcely walk,
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 and chickens that were as colourful as parrots. The farmer who
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 had built up this place had a great many strange ideas about
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 farming, but he had succeeded so much better with his
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 strange idea\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 s than any of his neighbours with their sensible
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 ones, that few had the courage to tell him what a fool he was.
\par 
