\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 WHILE I WAS ILL I had never paid much attention to the
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 people who brought our food, though when I reflected on it I
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 was able to recall them clearly, as I recall everything. Once
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 our ser\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 ver had been a Pelerine\hich\f2 \emdash \loch\f2 she who had talked to me the
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 night before. At other times they had been the shaven-
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 headed male slaves, or postulants in brown. This evening, the
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 evening of the day on which Melito had told his story, our
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 suppers were carried in by \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 a postulant I had not seen before,
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 a slender, grey-eyed girl. I got up and helped her to pass
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 around the trays.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 When we were finished, she thanked me and said, "You
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 will not be here much longer."
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 I told her I had something to do here, and nowhere else t\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 o
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 go.
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "You have your legion. If it has been destroyed, you will
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 be assigned to a new one."
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "I am not a soldier. I came north with some thought of
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 enlisting, but I fell sick before I got the opportunity."
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "You could have waited in your native town. I'm t\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 old that
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 recruiting parties go to all the towns, twice a year at least."
\par 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "My native town is Nessus, I'm afraid." I saw her smile.
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "But I left it some time ago, and I wouldn't have wanted to
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 sit around someplace else for half a year waiting. Anyway, I
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 neve\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 r thought of it. Are you from Nessus too?"
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "You're having trouble standing up."
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "No, I'm fine."
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 She touched my arm, a timid gesture that somehow reminded 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 me of the tame deer in the Autarch's garden.
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "You're swaying. Even if your fever is gone, you're \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 no longer
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 used to being on your feet. You have to realize that. You've
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 been abed for several days. I want you to lie down again
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 now."
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "If I do that, there'll be no one to talk to except the
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 people I've been talking with all day. The man on my right is
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 an \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Ascian prisoner, and the man on my left comes from some
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 village neither you nor I ever heard of."
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "All right, if you'll lie down I'll sit and talk to you for a
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 while. I've nothing more to do until the nocturne must be
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 played anyway. What quarter of Nessus\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2  do you come from?"
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 As she escorted me to my cot, I told her that I did not
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 want to talk, but to listen; and I asked her what quarter she
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 herself called home.
\par 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "When you're with the Pelerines, that's your home\hich\f2 \emdash \loch\f2 wherever 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 the tents are set up. The order be\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 comes your family and
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 your friends, just as if all your friends had suddenly become
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 your sisters too. But before I came here, I lived in the far
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 north western part of the city, within easy sight of the Wall."
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "Near the Sanguinary Field?"
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "Yes, very near\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2  it. Do you know the place?"
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "I fought there once.'
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Her eyes widened. "Did you, really? We used to go there
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 and watch. We weren't supposed to, but we did anyway. Did
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 you win?"
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 I had never thought about that and had to consider it.
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "No," I said after a \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 moment. "I lost."
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "But you lived. It's better, surely, to lose and live than to
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 take another man's life."
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 I opened my robe and showed her the scar on my chest
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 that Agilus's avern leaf had made.
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "You were very lucky. Often they bring in soldiers with
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 ch\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 est wounds like that, but we are seldom able to save
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 them." Hesitantly she touched my chest. There was a sweetness 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 in her face that I have not seen in the faces of other
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 women. For a moment she stroked my skin, then she jerked
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 her hand away. "It could not\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2  have been very deep."
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "It wasn't," I told her.
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "Once I saw a combat between an officer and an exultant
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 in masquerade. They used poisoned plants for weapons\hich\f2 \emdash \loch\f2 I
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 suppose because the officer would have had an unfair advantage 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 with the sword. The exultant wa\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 s killed and I left, but
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 afterward there was a great hullabaloo because the officer had
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 run amok. He came dashing by me, striking out with his
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 plant, but someone threw a cudgel at his legs and knocked
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 him down. I think that was the most exciting fight I ev\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 er
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 saw."
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "Did they fight bravely?"
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "Not really. There was a lot of argument about legalities\hich\f2 \emdash 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 you know how men do when they don't want to begin."
\par 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 " I shall be honoured to the end of my days to have been
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 thought worthy of such a challenge, which no othe\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 r bird has
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 ever received before. It is with the most profound regret that
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 I must tell you I cannot accept, and that for three reasons,
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 the first of which is that though you have feathers on your
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 wings, as you say, it is not against your wings that I would
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 fight.' Do you know that story?"
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Smiling, she shook her head.
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "It's a good one. I'll tell it to you some time. If you lived
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 so near the Sanguinary Field, your family must have been an
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 important one. Are you an armigette?"
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "Practically all of us are arm\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 igettes or exultants. It's a
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 rather aristocratic order, I'm afraid. Occasionally an optimate's 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 daughter like me is admitted, when the optimate has
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 been a long time friend of the order, but there are only three
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 of us. I'm told some optimates think all they\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2  have to do is
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 make a large gift and their girls will be accepted, but it really
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 isn't so\hich\f2 \emdash \loch\f2 they have to help out in various ways, not just with
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 money, and they have to have done it for a long time. The
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 world, you see, is not really- as corrupt as people lik\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 e to
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 believe."
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 I asked, "Do you think it is right to limit your order in that
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 way? You serve the Conciliator. Did he ask the people he
