\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "Severian."                                   
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "I'm Ava. Severian is one of those brother\hich\f2 \emdash \loch\f2 sister names,
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 isn't it? Severian and Severa. Do you have a sister?\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "I don't know. If I do, she's a witch."
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Ava let that pass. "The other one. Does she have a name?"
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "You know she's a woman then."
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "Uh huh. When I was serving the food, I thought for a
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 moment that one of the exultant sisters had come to help
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 me. Then \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 I looked around and it was you. At first it seemed
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 that it was just when I saw you from the corner of my eye,
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 but sometimes, while we've been sitting here, I see her even
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 when I'm looking right at you. When you glance to one side
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 sometimes you vanish, and \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 there's a tall, pale woman using
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 your face. Please don't tell me I fast overmuch. That's what
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 they all tell me, and it isn't true, and even if it were, this isn't
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 that."
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "Her name is Thecla. Do you remember what you were
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 just saying about losing humanity\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 ? Were you trying to tell
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 me about her?"
