\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 THAT NIGHT THERE WAS much talk of Foila's story, and this
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 time it was I who\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2  postponed making any judgment among
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 the tales. Indeed, I had formed a sort of horror of judging,
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 the residue, perhaps, of my education among the torturers,
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 who teach their apprentices from boyhood to execute the
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 instructions of the judges appointed (as th\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 ey themselves are
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 not) by the officials of our Commonwealth.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 In addition, I had something more pressing on my mind. I
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 had hoped that our evening meal would be served by Ava,
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 but when it was not, I rose anyway, dressed myself in my own
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 clothes, and slippe\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 d off in the gathering dark.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 It was a surprise\hich\f2 \emdash \loch\f2 a very pleasant one\hich\f2 \emdash \loch\f2 to find that my legs
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 were strong again. I had been free of fever for several days,
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 yet I had grown accustomed to thinking myself ill (just as I
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 had earlier been accustomed to thinking mys\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 elf well) and had
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 lain in my cot without complaint. No doubt many a man
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 who walks about and does his work is dying and ignorant of
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 it, and many who lie abed all day are healthier than those
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 who bring their food and wash them.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 I tried to recall, as I foll\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 owed the winding paths between
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 the tents, when I had felt so well before. Not in the mountains 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 or upon the lake\hich\f2 \emdash \loch\f2 the hardships I had suffered there
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 had gradually reduced my vitality until I fell prey to the
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 fever. Not when I fled Thrax, for I was already w\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 orn out from
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 my duties as lictor. Not when I had arrived at Thrax; Dorcas
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 and I had undergone privations in the roadless country nearly
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 as severe as I was to bear alone in the mountains. Not even
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 when I had been at the House Absolute (a period that now
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 see\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 med as remote as the reign of Ymar), because I had still
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 been suffering the after effects of the alzabo and my ingestion
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 of Thecla's dead memories.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 At last it came to me: I felt now as I had on that memorable 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 morning when Agia and I had set out for the \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Botanic
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Gardens, the first morning after I had left the Citadel. That
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 morning, though I had not known it, I had acquired the
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Claw. For the first time -I wondered if it had not been cursed
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 as well as blessed. Or perhaps it was only that all the past
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 months \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 had been needed for me to recover fully from the
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 leaf of the avern that had pierced me that same evening. I
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 took out the Claw and stared at its silvery gleam, and when I
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 raised my eyes, I saw the glowing scarlet of the Pelerines'
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 chapel.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 I could hear the\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2  chanting, and I knew it would be some
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 time before the chapel would be empty, but I proceeded
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 anyway, and at last slipped through the door and took a place
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 in the back. Of the liturgy of the Pelerines, I will say nothing.
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Such things cannot always be well \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 described, and even when
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 they can, it is less than proper to do so. The guild called the
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Seekers for Truth and Penitence, to which I at one time
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 belonged, has its own ceremonies, one of which I have de-
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 scribed in some detail in another place. Certainly th\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 ose cere-
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 monies are peculiar to it, and perhaps those of the Pelerines
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 were peculiar to them as well, though they may once have
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 been universal.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Speaking in so far as I can as an unprejudiced observer, I
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 would say that they were more beautiful than ours \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 but less
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 theatrical, and thus in the long run perhaps less moving, The
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 costumes of the participants were ancient, I am sure, and
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 striking. The chants possessed a queer attraction I have not
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 encountered in other music. Our ceremonies were intended
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 chiefly t\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 o impress the role of the guild upon the minds of our
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 younger members. Possibly those of the Pelerines had a similar 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 function. If not, then they were designed to engage the
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 particular attention of the All-Seeing, and whether they did
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 so I cannot say. In t\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 he event, the order received no special
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 protection.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 When the ceremony was over and the scarlet-clad priestesses 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 filed out, I bowed my head and feigned to be deep in
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 prayer. Very readily, I found, the pretence became the thing
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 itself. I remained consciou\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 s of my kneeling body, but only as
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 a peripheral burden. My mind was among the starry wastes,
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 far from Urth and indeed far from Urth's archipelago of island 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 worlds, and it seemed to me that that to which I spoke
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 was farther still\hich\f2 \emdash \loch\f2 I had come, as it were, to\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2  the walk of the
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 universe, and now shouted through the walls to one who
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 waited outside.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "Shouted," I said, but perhaps that is the wrong word
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Rather I whispered, as Bamoch, perhaps, walled up in his
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 house, might have whispered through some chink to a sym\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 pathetic 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 passerby. I spoke of what I had been when I wore a
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 ragged shirt and watched the beasts and birds through the
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 narrow window of the mausoleum, and what I had become. I
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 spoke too, not of Vodalus and his struggle against the Autarch, 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 but of the moti\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 ves I had once foolishly attributed to
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 him. I did not deceive myself with the thought that I had it
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 in me to lead millions. I asked only that I might lead myself;
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 and as I did so, I seemed to see, with a vision increasingly
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 clear, through the chink in the \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 universe to a new universe
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 bathed in golden light, where my listener knelt to hear me.
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 What had seemed a crevice in the world had expanded until
\par 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 I could see a face and folded hands, and the opening, like a
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 tunnel, running deep into a human head that for a\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2  time
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 seemed larger than the head of Typhon carved upon the
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 mountain. I was whispering into my own ear, and when I
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 realized it I flew into it like a bee and stood up.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Everyone was gone, and a silence as profound as any I have
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 ever heard seemed to hang in\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2  the air with the incense. The
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 altar rose before me, humble in comparison to that Agia and
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 I had destroyed, yet beautiful with its lights and purity of
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 line and panels of sunstone and lapis lazuli.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Now I came forward and knelt before it. I needed no
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 scho\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 lar to tell me the Theologoumenon was no nearer now.
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Yet he seemed nearer, and I was able\hich\f2 \emdash \loch\f2 for the final time\hich\f2 \emdash \loch\f2 to
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 take out the Claw, something I had feared I could not do.
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Forming the syllables only in my mind, I said, "I have carried
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 you over many mountains\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 , across rivers, and across the pampas, 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 You have given Thecla life in me. You have given me
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Dorcas, and you have restored Jonas to this world. Surely I
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 have no complaint of you, though you must have many of
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 me. One I shall not deserve. It shall not be sai\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 d that I did not-
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 do what I might to undo the harm I have done."
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 I knew the Claw would be swept away if I were to leave it
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 openly on the altar. Mounting the dais, I searched among its
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 furnishings for a place of concealment that should be secure
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 and perma\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 nent, and at last noticed that the altar-stone itself
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 was held from below with four clamps that had surely never
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 been loosed since the altar was constructed, and seemed
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 likely to remain in place so long as it stood. I have strong
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 hands, and I was able to f\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 ree them, though I do not think
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 most men could. Beneath the stone some wood had been
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 chiselled away so that it should be supported at the edges
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 only and would not rock\hich\f2 \emdash \loch\f2 it was more than I had dared to
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 hope for. With Jonas's razor I cut a small square of clo\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 th
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 from the edge of my now-tattered guild cloak. In it I wrap-
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 ped the daw, then I laid it under the stone and retightened
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 the clamps, bloodying my fingers in my effort to make sure
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 they would not come loose by accident.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 As I stepped away from the altar \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 I felt a profound sorrow,
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 but I had not gone halfway to the door of the chapel before I
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 was seized with wild joy. The burden of life and death had
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 been lifted from me. Now I was only a man again, and I was
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 delirious with delight. I felt as I had felt as a \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 child when the
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 long lessons with Master Malrubius were over and I was free
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 to play in the Old Yard or clamber across, the broken curtain
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 wall to run among the trees and mausoleums of our necropolis. 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 I was disgraced and outcast and homeless, without
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 friend\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2  and without money, and I had just given up the most
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 valuable object in the world, which was, perhaps, in the end
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 the only valuable object in the world. And yet I knew that all
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 would be well. I had climbed to the bottom of existence and
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 felt it with my han\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 ds, and I knew that there was a bottom,
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 and that from this point onward I could only rise. I swirled
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 my cloak about me as I had when I was an actor, for I knew
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 that I was an actor and no torturer, though I had been a
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 torturer. I leaped into the air and cap\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 ered as the goats do on
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 the mountainside, for I knew that I was a child, and that no
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 man can be a man who is not.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Outside, the cool air seemed expressly made for me, a new
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 creation and not the ancient atmosphere of Urth. I bathed in
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 it, first spreading m\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 y cloak then raising my arms to the stars,
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 filled my lungs as does one who has just escaped drowning in
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 the fluids of birth.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 All this took less time than it has required to describe it,
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 and I was about to start back to the lazaret tent from which I
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 had c\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 ome when I became aware of a motionless figure watching 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 me from the shadows of another tent some distance off.
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Ever since the boy and I had escaped the blindly questing
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 creature that had destroyed the village of the magicians, I
