\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 with sharp eyes will be counting us, and the contracts
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 usually call for men."
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "Guasacht said there'd be more money today,' I reminded
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 him.
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 He cleared his throat and spat, the white phlegm vanishing
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 into th\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 e clammy air as though Urth herself had swallowed it.
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "They won't pay until it's over. They never do."
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Guasacht shouted and waved an arm; Erblon gestured
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 with our flag, and we were off, the hoofbeats sounding like
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 the thudding of a hundred muffled drums.\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2  I said, "I suppose
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 that way they don't have to pay for those who are killed."
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "They pay triple-once because he fought, once for blood
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 money, and once for discharge money."
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "Or she fought, I suppose."
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Mesrop spat again.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 We rode for some time, then halt\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 ed at a spot that seemed
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 no different from any other. As the column fell silent, I heard
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 a humming or murmuring in the hills all around us. A scattered army, 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 dispersed no doubt for sanitary reasons and to
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 deprive the Ascian enemy of a concentrated target,\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2  was assembling 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 now just as particles of dust in the stone town had
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 come together in the bodies of its resuscitated dancers.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Not unnoticed. Even as birds of prey had once followed us
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 before we reached that town, now five-armed shapes that
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 spun like whee\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 ls pursued us above the scattered clouds that
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 dimmed and melted in the level red light of dawn. At first,
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 when they were highest, they seemed merely grey; but as we
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 watched they dropped toward us, and I saw they were of a
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 hue for which I can find no name b\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 ut that stands to achroma
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 as gold to yellow, or silver to white. The air groaned with
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 their turning.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Another that we had not seen came leaping across our
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 path, hardly higher than the treetops. Each spoke was the
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 length of a tower, pierced with casements \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 and ports. Though
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 it lay flat upon the air, it seemed to stride along. Its wind
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 whistled down upon us as if to blow away the trees. My
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 piebald screamed and bolted, and so did many other destriers, 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 often falling in that strange wind.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 In the space of a he\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 artbeat it was over. The leaves that had
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 swirled about us like snow fell to earth. Guasacht shouted
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 and Erblon sounded the graisle and brandished our flag. I got
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 the piebald under control and cantered from one destrier to
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 another, taking them by the nostri\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 ls until their riders could
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 manage them again.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 I rescued Daria, who I had not known was in the column,
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 in this way. She looked very pretty and boyish dressed as a
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 trooper, with a contus, and a slender sabre at either side of
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 her saddle horn. I could not \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 help thinking when I saw her of
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 how other women I had known would appear in the same
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 situation: Thea a theatrical warrior maid, beautiful and dramatic 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 but essentially the figure of a figurehead; Thecla\hich\f2 \emdash \loch\f2 how
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 part of myself\hich\f2 \emdash \loch\f2 a vengeful mimalone brandishing po\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 isoned
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 weapons; Agia astride a slender-legged sorrel, wearing a cuirass 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 moulded to her figure, while her hair, plaited with bow-
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 strings, flew wild in the wind; Jolenta a floriate queen in
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 armour spikey with thorns, her big breasts and fleshy thighs
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 absur\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 d at any gait faster than a walk, smiling dreamily at each
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 halt and attempting to recline in the saddle; Dorcas a naiad
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 riding, lifted momentarily like a fountain flashing with sun-
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 shine; Valeria, perhaps, an aristocratic Daria.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 I had supposed, when I s\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 aw our people scatter, that it
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 would be impossible to reassemble the column; but within a
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 few moments of the time the pentadactyl air-strider had
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 passed over us, we were together again. We galloped for a
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 league or more\hich\f2 \emdash \loch\f2 mostly, I suspect, to dissipate some \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 of the
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 nervous energy of our destriers\hich\f2 \emdash \loch\f2 then halted by a brook and
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 gave them just as much water as would wet their mouths
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 without making them sluggish. When I had fought the
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 piebald back from the bank, I rode to a clearing from which I
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 could watch the sky. \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Soon Guasacht trotted over and asked
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 me jocularly, "You looking for another one?"
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 I nodded and told him 1 had never seen such craft before.
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "You wouldn't have, unless you've been close to the front.
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 They'd never come back if they tried to go down south."
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "Soldiers like us wouldn't stop them."
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 He grew suddenly serious, his tiny eyes mere slits in the
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 sun-browned flesh. "No. But plucky lads can stop their raiding 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 parties. The guns and air-galleys can't do that."
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 The piebald stirred and stamped with imp\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 atience. I said,
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "I come from a part of the city you've probably never heard
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 of, the Citadel. There are guns there that look out over the
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 whole quarter, but I've never known them to be fired except
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 ceremonially." Still staring at the sky, I thought of the \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 wheeling 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 pentadactyls over Nessus, and a thousand blasts, issuing
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 not just from the Barbican and the Great Keep, but from all
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 the towers; and I wondered with what weapons the pentadactyls 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 would reply.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "Come along," Guasacht said. "I know it's a temptat\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 ion to
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 keep a lookout for them, but it doesn't do any good."
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 I followed him back to the brook, where Erblon was lining
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 up the column. "They didn't even fire at us. They must
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 surely have guns in those fliers."
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "We're pretty small fish." I could see that G\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 uasacht
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 wanted me to rejoin the column, though he hesitated to
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 order me to do so directly.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 For my part, I could feel fear grip me like a spectre, strongest 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 about my legs, but lifting cold tentacles into my bowels,
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 touching my heart. I wanted to be silen\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 t, but I could
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 not stop talking. "When we go onto the field of battle-"
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 (I think I imagined this field like the shaven lawn of the
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Sanguinary Field, where I had fought Agilus.)
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Guasacht laughed. "When we go into the fight, our gunners 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 would be delighted \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 to see them out after us." Before I
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 understood what he was about to do, he struck the piebald
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 with the flat of his blade and sent me cantering off.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Fear is like those diseases that disfigure the face with running 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 sores. One becomes almost more afraid of\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2  their being
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 seen than of their source, and comes to feel not only disgraced 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 but defiled. When the piebald began to slow, I dug
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 my heels into him and fell into line at the very end of the
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 column.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Only a short time before I had been on the point of repla\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 cing 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Erblon; now I was demoted, hot by Guasacht but by
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 myself, to the lowest position. And yet when I had helped
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 reassemble the scattered troopers, the thing I feared had al-
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 ready passed; so that the entire drama of my elevation had
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 been played out after\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2  it had ended in debasement. It was as
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 though one were to see a young man idling in a public garden
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 stabbed\hich\f2 \emdash \loch\f2 then watch him, all unknowing, strike up an acquaintance 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 with the voluptuous wife of his murderer, and at
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 last, having ascertained, as he thought, \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 that her husband was
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 in another part of the city, clasp her to him until she cried
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 out from the pain of the dagger's hilt protruding from his
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 chest.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 When the column lurched forward, Daria detached herself
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 from it and waited until she could fall in beside\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2  me. "You're
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 afraid," she said. It was not a question but a statement, and
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 not a reproach but almost a password, like the ridiculous
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 phrases I had learned at Vodalus's banquet.
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "Yes. You're about to remind me of the boast I made to
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 you in the forest. I ca\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 n only say that I did not know it to be
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 an empty one when I made it. A certain wise man once tried
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 to teach me that even after a client has mastered one excruciation, 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 so that he can put it from his mind even while he
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 screams and writhes, another quite dif\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 ferent excruciation
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 may be as effectual in breaking his will as in breaking a
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 child's. I learned to explain all this when he asked me but
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 never until now to apply it, as I should, to my own life. But if
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 I am the client here, who is the torturer?"
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "We're a\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 ll more or less afraid," she said. "That was why-
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 yes, I saw it\hich\f2 \emdash \loch\f2 Guasacht sent you away. It was to keep you
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 from making his own feeling worse. If it were worse, he
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 wouldn't be able to lead. When the time comes, you'll do
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 what you have to, and that's all any\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2  of them do."
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "Hadn't we better go?" I asked. The end of the column
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 was moving off in that surging way the tail of a long line
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 always does.
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "If we go now, a lot of them will know we're at the rear
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 because we're afraid. If we wait just a little while long\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 er,
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 many of those who saw you talking with Guasacht will think
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 he sent you back here to speed up stragglers, and that I came
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 back to be with you."
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "All right," I said.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Her hand, damp with sweat and as thin as Dorcas's, came
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 sliding into mine.
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Until tha\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 t moment, I had been certain she had fought
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 before. Now I asked her, "Is this your first time too?"
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "I can fight better than most of them," she declared, "and
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 I'm sick of being called a whore."
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Together, we trotted after the column.
\par 
