\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 strange steeds were Ascians; our maneuver had been \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 intended
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 to prevent them from taking the peltasts in the flank, and
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 had now succeeded in that they would now have to make
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 their attack, if they could, through us. There seemed to be
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 about five thousand of them, however, and there were certainly 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 many more \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 than we had fit to fight.
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Yet no attack came. We had halted and formed a tight
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 line, stirrup to stirrup. Despite their numbers, they surged
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 nervously up and down before it as though attracted first by
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 the thought of passing it on the right, then on the le\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 ft, then
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 on the right again. It was clear, however, that they could not
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 pass at all unless a part of their force engaged our front to
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 prevent our striking the rest from behind. As if hoping to
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 postpone the fight, we did not fire..
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Now we saw repetitions \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 of the behavior of the lone spearman 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 who had left his square to attack us. One of the tall men
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 dashed forward. In one hand he held a slender-staff, hardly
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 more than a switch; in the other, a sword of the kind called a
\par }{\i\dbch\af23 \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 shotel}{\dbch\af23 \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 , which has a very long, double\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 -edged blade whose for-
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 ward half is curved into a semicircle. As he drew nearer he
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 slowed, and I saw that his eyes were unfocused; that he was in
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 fact blind. The dwarf on his shoulders had an arrow nocked
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 to the string of a short, recurved bow.
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 When thes\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 e two were within half a chain of us, Erblon
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 detailed two men to drive them off. Before they could close
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 with the blind man, he broke into a run as swift as any destriers 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 but eerily silent, and came flying toward us. Eight or
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 ten troopers fired, but I saw\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2  then how difficult it is to hit a
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 target moving at such speed. The arrow struck and burst in a
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 blaze of orange light. A trooper tried to parry the blind man's
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 wand\hich\f2 \emdash \loch\f2 the shotel flashed down, and its hooked blade laid
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 open the trooper's skull.
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Then a group\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2  of three of the blind men with three riders
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 detached itself from the mass of the enemy. Before they
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 reached us, there were clusters of five or six coming. Far
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 down the line, our hipparch raised his arm; Guasacht waved
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 us forward and Erblon blew the charge\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 , echoed to right and
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 left\hich\f2 \emdash \loch\f2 a bellowing note that seemed to have deep-mouthed
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 bells in it.
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Though I did not know it at the time, it is axiomatic that
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 encounters purely between cavalry rapidly degenerate into
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 mere skirmishes. So it was with ours. We rode at\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2  them, and
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 though we lost twenty or thirty in doing so, we rode through
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 them. At once we turned to engage them again, both to
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 prevent their flanking the peltasts and to regain contact with
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 our own army. They, of course, turned to face us; and in a
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 short ti\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 me neither we nor they had anything that could be
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 called a front, or any tactics beyond those each fighter forged
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 for himself.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 My own were to veer away from any dwarf who looked
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 ready to shoot and try to catch others from behind or from
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 the side. They wo\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 rked well enough when I could apply them,
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 but I quickly found that though the dwarfs appeared almost
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 helpless when the blind men they rode were killed under
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 them, their tall steeds ran amok without their riders, attacking 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 anything that stood in their path\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2  with frantic energy, so
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 that they were more dangerous than ever.
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Very soon the dwarfs' arrows and our conti had kindled
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 scores of fires in the grass. The choking smoke rendered the
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 confusion worse than ever. I had lost sight of Daria and
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Guasacht\hich\f2 \emdash \loch\f2 of ever\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 yone I knew\hich\f2 \emdash \loch\f2 sometime before. Through
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 the acrid grey haze I could just make out a figure on a plunging 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 destrier fighting off four Ascians. I went to him, and
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 though one dwarf turned his blind steed and sent an arrow
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 whizzing by my ear, I rode over them and\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2  heard the blind
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 man's bones snap under the piebald's hoofs. A hairy figure
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 rose from the smouldering grass behind the other pw and cut
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 them down as a peon hews a tree\hich\f2 \emdash \loch\f2 three or four strokes of his
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 axe to the same spot until the blind man fell.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 The mounte\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 d soldier I had come to rescue was not one of
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 our troopers, but one of the savages who had been on our
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 right earlier. He had been wounded, and when I saw the
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 blood I recalled that I had been wounded too. My leg was
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 stiff, my strength nearly gone. I would h\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 ave ridden back
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 toward the south crest of the valley and our own lines if I had
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 known which way to go. As it was, I gave the piebald his head
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 and a good slap from the reins, having heard that these animals 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 will often return to the place where they last ha\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 d water
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 and rest. He broke into a canter that soon became a gallop.
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Once he jumped, nearly throwing me from the saddle, and I
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 looked down to glimpse a dead destrier with Erblon dead
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 beside him, and the brass graisle and the black and green flag
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 lying on th\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 e burning turf. I would have. turned the piebald
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 and gone back for them, but by the time I pulled him up, I
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 no longer knew the spot. To my right, a mounted line
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 showed through the smoke, dark and almost formless, but
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 serrated. Par behind it loomed a machin\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 e that flashed fire, a
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 machine that was like a tower walking.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 At one moment they were nearly invisible; at the next they
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 were upon me like a torrent. I cannot say who the riders were
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 or on what beasts they rode; not because I have forgotten
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 (for I forget\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2  nothing) but because I saw nothing clearly.
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 There was no question of fighting, only of seeking in some
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 way to live. I parried a blow from a twisted weapon that was
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 neither sword nor axe; the piebald reared, and I saw an arrow
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 protruding from his chest lik\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 e a horn of fire. A rider crashed
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 against us, and we fell into the dark.
