\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "In a short time you will be standing at its margin. You
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 asked when you would leave this planet. Not until your rule
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 here is secure. W\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 hen the city and the House Absolute obey
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 you and your armies have repelled the incursions of the slaves
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 of Erebus. Within a few years, perhaps. But perhaps not for
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 decades. We two will come for you."
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "You are the second tonight to tell me I will see you
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 again," I said. Just as I spoke, there was a slight shock, like
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 the sensation one feels when a boat is brought skillfully to
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 the dock. I walked down the pont and out upon sand. and
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Master Malrubius and Triskele followed me. I asked if they
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 would not stay w\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 ith me for a time to counsel me.
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "For a short time only. If you have further questions, you
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 must ask them now."
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 The silver tongue of the pont was already creeping back
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 into the hull. It seemed that it had hardly come home before
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 the ship lifted itself a\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 nd scudded down the same aperture in
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 reality into which the green man had run.
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "You spoke of the peace and justice that the New Sun is
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 to bring. Is there justice in his calling me so far? What is the
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 test I must pass?"
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "It is not he who calls you. Those \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 who call hope to summon 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 the New Sun to them," Master Malrubius said, but I
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 did not understand him. Then he recounted to me in brief
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 words the secret history of Time, which is the greatest of all
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 secrets, and which I will set down here in the proper place.
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 When he had finished, my mind reeled and I feared I would
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 forget all he had said, because it seemed too great a thing for
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 any living man to know, and because I had learned at last
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 that the mists close for me as for other men.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "You will not forget, you a\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 bove all. At Vodalus\hich\f2 \rquote \loch\f2 s banquet,
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 you said you felt sure you would forget the foolish passwords
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 he taught you in imitation of the words of authority. But you
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 did not. You will remember everything. Remember too, not
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 to be afraid. It may be that the epic penan\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 ce of mankind is at
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 an end. The old Autarch told you the truth-we will not go
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 to the stars again until we go as a divinity, but that time may
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 not be far off now. In you all the divergent tendencies of our
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 race may have achieved synthesis."
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Triskele stood\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2  on his hind legs for a moment as he used to,
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 then spun around and galloped down the starlit beach, three
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 paws scattering the little cat's-paw waves. When he was a
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 hundred strides off he turned and looked back at me, as
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 though he wished me to follow.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 I t\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 ook a few steps toward him, but Master Malrubius said,
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "You cannot go where he is going, Severian. I know you
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 think us cacogens of a kind, and for a time I felt it would not
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 be wise to wholly undeceive you, but I must do so now. We
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 are aquastors, beings cr\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 eated and sustained by the power of
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 the imagination and the concentration of thought."
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "I have heard of such things," I told him. "But I have
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 touched you."
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "That is no test. We are as solid as most truly false things
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 are\hich\f2 \emdash \loch\f2 a dance of particles in space. On\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 ly the things no one can
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 touch are true, as you should know by now. Once you met a
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 woman named Cyriaca, who told you tales of the great thinking 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 machines of the past. There is such a machine on the ship
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 in which we sailed. It has the power to look into yo\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 ur mind."
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 I asked, "Are you that machine, then?" A feeling of loneliness 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 and vague fear grew in me.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "I am Master Malrubius, and Triskele is Triskele. The machine 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 looked among your memories and found us. Our lives
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 in your mind are not so complete as th\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 ose of Thecla and the
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 old Autarch, but we are there nevertheless, and live while you
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 live. But we are maintained in the physical world by the
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 energies of the machine, and its range is but a few thousand
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 years."
\par \tab 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 As he spoke these final words, his flesh w\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 as already fading
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 into bright dust. For a moment it glinted in the cold star-
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 light. Then it was gone. Triskele remained with me a few
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 breaths longer, and when his. yellow coat was already silvered
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 and blowing away in the gentle breeze, I heard his bark.
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Then I stood alone at the edge of the sea I had longed for
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 so often; but though I was alone, I found it cheering, and
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 breathed the air that is like no other, and smiled to hear the
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 soft song of the little waves. Land\hich\f2 \emdash \loch\f2 Nessus, the House Absolute, 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 and all th\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 e rest\hich\f2 \emdash \loch\f2 lay to the east; west lay the sea; I
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 walked north because I was reluctant to leave it too soon,
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 and because Triskele had run in that direction, along the
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 margin of the sea. There great Abaia might wallow with his
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 women, yet the sea was older far, an\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 d wiser than he; we human 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 beings, like all the life of the land, had come from the
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 sea; and because we could not conquer it, it was ours always.
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 The old, red sun rose on my right and touched the waves
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 with his fading beauty, and I heard the calling of the\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2  sea
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 tods, the innumerable birds.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 By the time the shadows were short, I was tired. My face
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 and my wounded leg pained me; I had not eaten since noon
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 of the previous day and had not slept save for my trance in
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 the Ascian tent. I would have rested if I coul\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 d, but the sun
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 was warm, and the line of cliffs beyond the beach offered no
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 shade. At last I followed the tracks of a two-wheeled cart and
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 came to a clump of wild roses growing from a dune. There I
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 halted, and seated myself in their shadow to take off my
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 b\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 oots and pour out the sand that had entered their splitting
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 seams.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 A thorn caught my forearm and broke from its branch,
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 remaining embedded in my skin, with a scariet drop of blood,
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 no bigger than a grain of millet, at its tip. I plucked it out-
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 then fell\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2  to my knees.                            
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 It was the Claw.
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 The claw perfect, shining black, just as I had placed it
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 under the altar stone of the Pelerines. All that bush and all
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 the other bushes growing with it were covered with white
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 blossoms and these \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 perfect Claws. The one in my palm
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 flamed with transplendent light as I looked at it.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 I had surrendered the Claw, but I had retained the little
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 leather sack Dorcas had sewn for it I took it from my
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 sabretache and hung it about my neck in the old way, with
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 the claw once more inside. It was only when I had thus put
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 it away that I recalled seeing just such a bush in the Botanic
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Gardens at the beginning of my journey.
\par \tab 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 No one can explain such things. Since I have come to the
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 House Absolute, I have talked wit\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 h the heptarch and with
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 various acaryas; but they have been able to tell me very little
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 save that the Increate has chosen before this to manifest
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 himself in these plants.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 At that time I did not think of it, being filled with won-
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 der\hich\f2 \emdash \loch\f2 but may it not be th\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 at we were guided to the unfinished
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Sand Garden? I carried the Claw even then, though I did not
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 know it; Agia had already slipped it under the closure of my
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 sabretache. Might it not be that we came to the unfinished
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 garden so that the Claw, flying as it we\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 re against the wind of
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Time, might make its farewell? The idea is absurd. But then,
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 all ideas are absurd.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 What struck me on the beach\hich\f2 \emdash \loch\f2 and it struck me indeed, so
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 that I slavered as at a blow\hich\f2 \emdash \loch\f2 was that if the Eternal Principle 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 had rested in that curved th\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 orn I had carried about my
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 neck across so many leagues, and if it now rested in the new
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 thorn (perhaps the same thorn) I had only now put there,
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 then it might rest in anything, and in fact probably did rest
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 in everything, in every thorn on every bush, in e\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 very drop of
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Water in the sea. The thorn was a sacred Claw because all
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 thorns were sacred Claws; the sand in my boots was sacred
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 sand because it came from a beach of sacred sand. The
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 cenobites treasured up the relics of the sannyasins because
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 the sannyasin\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 s had approached the Pancreator. But every-
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 thing had approached and even touched the Pancreator, because 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 everything had dropped from his hand. Everything was
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 a relic. All the world was a relic. I drew off my boots, that had
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 travelled with me so far, and \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 threw them into the waves that I
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 might not walk shod on holy ground.
\par 
