\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 AND I WALKED ON as a mighty army, for I felt myself in the
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 company of all those who walked in me. I was surrounded by
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 a numerous guard; and I was the guard about th\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 e person of
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 the monarch. There were women in my ranks, smiling and
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 grim, and children who ran and laughed and, daring Erebus
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 and Abaia, hurled seashells into the sea.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 In half a day I came to the mouth of Gyoll, so wide that
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 the farther shore was lost in \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 distance. Three-sided isles lay in
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 it, and through them vessels with billowing sails picked their
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 way like clouds among the peaks of the mountains. I hailed
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 one passing the point on which I stood and asked for passage
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 to Nessus. A wild figure I must have a\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 ppeared, with my
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 scarred face and tattered cloak and every rib showing.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Her captain sent a boat for me nonetheless, a kindness I
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 have not forgotten. I saw fear and awe in the eyes of the
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 rowers. Perhaps it was only at the sight of my half-healed
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 wounds; \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 but they were men who had seen many wounds, and
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 I recalled how I had felt when I first saw the face of the
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Autarch in the House Azure, though he was not a tall man,
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Or even a man, truly.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Twenty days and nights the Sammru made her way up
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Gyoll. We sailed \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 when we could, and rowed, a dozen sweeps
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 to a side, when we could not. It was a hard passage for the
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 sailors, for though the current is almost imperceptibly slow, it
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 runs day and night, and so long and so wide are the meanders
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 of the channel, that an oarsm\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 an often sees at evening the spot
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 from which he laboured When the beating of the drum first
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 roused the watch.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 For me it was as pleasant as a yachting expedition. Although 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 I offered to make sail and row with the rest, they
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 would not permit it. Then I tol\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 d the captain, a sly-faced man
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 who looked as though he lived by bargaining as much as by
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 sailing, that I would pay him well when we reached Nessus;
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 but he would not hear of it, and insisted (pulling at his mustache, 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 which he did whenever he wished to show\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2  the greatest
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 sincerity) that my presence was reward enough for him and
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 his crew. I do not believe they guessed I was their Autarch,
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 and for fear of such as Vodalus had been I was careful to
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 drop no hints to them; but from my eyes and manner they
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 seemed to\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2  feel I was an adept.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 The incident of the captain's sword must have strengthened 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 their superstition. It was a craquemarte, the heaviest of
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 the sea swords, with a blade as wide as my palm, sharply
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 curved and graven with stars and suns and other things th\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 e
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 captain did not understand. He wore it when we were close
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 enough to a riverbank village or another ship to make him
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 feel the occasion demanded dignity; but for the most part he
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 left it lying on the little quarterdeck. I found it there, and
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 having nothing\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2  else to do but watch sticks and fruit skins bob
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 in the green water, I took out my half stone and sharpened it.
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 After a time he saw me testing the edge with my thumb and.
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 began to boast of his swordsmanship. Since the craquemarte
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 was at least two-thirds th\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 e weight of Terminus Est, with a
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 short grip, it was amusing to hear him; I listened with delight
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 for half a watch or so. As it happened there was a hempen
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 cable about the thickness of my wrist coiled nearby, and
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 when he began to lose interest in his own in\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 ventions, I had
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 him and the mate hold up three cubits or so between them.
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 The craquemarte severed it like a hair; then before either of
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 them could recover breath, I threw it flashing toward the sun
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 and caught it by the hilt.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 As I fear that incident shows\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2  too well, I was beginning to
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 feel better. There is nothing to enthrall the reader in rest,
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 fresh air, and plain food; but they can work wonders against
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 wounds and exhaustion.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 The captain would have given me his cabin if I had let
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 him, but I slept on dec\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 k rolled in my cloak, and on our one
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 night of rain found shelter under the boat, which was stowed
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 bottom-up amidships. As I learned on board, it is the nature
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 of breezes to die when Urth turns her back to the sun; so I
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 went to sleep, on most nights, with t\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 he chant of the rowers in
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 my ears. In the morning I woke to the rattle of the anchor
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 chain.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Sometimes, though, I woke before morning, when we lay
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 close to shore with only a sleepy lookout on deck. And sometimes 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 the moonlight roused me to find us gliding\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2  forward
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 under reefed sails, with the mate steering and the watch
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 asleep beside the halyards. On one such night, shortly after
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 we had passed through the Wall, I went aft and saw the
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 phosphorescence of our wake like cold fire on the dark water
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 and thought f\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 or a moment that the man-apes of the mine
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 were coming to be cured by the Claw, or to gain an old
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 revenge. That, of course, was not truly strange\hich\f2 \emdash \loch\f2 only the
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 foolish error of a mind still half in dream. What happened
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 the next morning was not truly strange eith\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 er, but it affected
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 me deeply.
\par 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 The oarsmen were rowing a slow beat to get us around a
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 leagues-long bend to a point where we could catch what little
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 wind there was. The sound of the drum and the hissing of
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 the water falling from the long blades of the swee\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 ps are hypnotic, 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 I think because they are so similar to the beating of
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 one's own heart in sleep and the sound the blood makes as it
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 moves past the inner ear on its way to the brain.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 I was standing by the rail looking at the shore, still marshy
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 here wher\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 e the plains of old have been flooded by silt-choked
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Gyoll; and it seemed to me that I saw forms in the hillocks
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 and hummocks, as though all that vast, soft wilderness had a
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 geometrical soul (as certain pictures do) that vanished when I
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 stared at it, then \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 reappeared when I took my eyes away. The
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 captain came to stand beside me, and I told him I had heard
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 that the ruins of the city extended far downriver and asked
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 when we would sight them. He laughed and explained that
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 we had been among them for the past two\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2  days, and loaned
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 me his glass so I could see that what I had taken for a stump
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 was in actuality a broken and tilted column covered with
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 moss.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 At once everything\hich\f2 \emdash \loch\f2 walls, streets, monuments\hich\f2 \emdash \loch\f2 seemed to
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 spring from hiding, just as the stone town had reconstru\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 cted
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 itself while we watched from the tomb roof with the two
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 witches. No change had occurred outside my own mind, but
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 I had been transported, far faster than Master Malrubius's
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 ship could have taken me, from the desolate countryside to
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 the midst of an anci\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 ent and immense ruin.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Even now I cannot help but wonder how much any of us
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 see of what is before us. For weeks my friend Jonas had
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 seemed to me only a man with a prosthetic hand, and when I
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 was with Baldanders and Dr. Talos, I had overlooked a hundred 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 c\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 lues that should have told me Baldanders was master.
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 How impressed I was outside the Piteous Gate because Baldanders 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 did not escape the doctor when he could.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 As the day wore on, the ruins became plainer and plainer
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 still. At each loop of the river, the \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 green walls rose higher,
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 from ever firmer ground. When I woke the next morning,
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 some of the stronger buildings retained their upper stories.
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Not long afterward, I saw a little boat, newly built, tied to an
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 ancient pier.. I pointed it out to the captain, wh\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 o smiled at
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 my naivety and said, "There are families who live, grandson
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 following grandsire, by sifting these ruins."
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "So I've been told, but that cannot be one of their boats.
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Its too small to take much loot away in."
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "Jewelry or coins. No one else goe\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 s ashore here. There's no
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 law\hich\f2 \emdash \loch\f2 the pillagers murder each other, and anyone else who
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 lands."
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "I must go there. Will you wait for me?"
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 He stared at me as though I were mad. "How long?"
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "Until noon. No later."
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 "Look," he said, and pointed. "Ahead is the la\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 st big bend.
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Leave us here and meet us there, where the channel bows
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 around again. It will be afternoon before we get there."
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 I agreed, and he had the }{\b\i\dbch\af23 \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Samru's}{\dbch\af23 \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2  boat put into the water
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 for me, and told four men to row me ashore. As we were
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 about to cast of\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 f, he unbelted his craquemarte and handed it
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 to me, saying solemnly, "It has stood by me in many a grim
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 fight. Go for their heads, but be careful not to knick the edge
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 on their belt buckles."
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 I accepted his sword with thanks, and told him I had always 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 fa\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 voured the neck. "That's good," he said, "if you don't
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 have shipmates by that might be hurt when you swing it
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 flat," and he pulled his mustache.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Sitting in the stern, I had ample opportunity to observe
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 the faces of my rowers, and it was plain they were n\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 early as
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 frightened of the shore as they were of me. They laid us
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 alongside the small boat, then nearly capsized their own in
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 their haste to be away. After determining that what I had
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 seen from the rail was in fact what I had taken it to be, a
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 wilted scarl\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 et poppy left lying on the single seat, I watched
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 them row back to the Samru and saw that though a light
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 wind now favoured the billowing mains'l, the sweeps had been
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 brought out and were beating a quick-stroke. Presumably the
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 captain planned to round the l\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 ong meander as swiftly as he
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 could; if I were not at the spot he had pointed out, he could
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 proceed without me, telling himself (and others, should others 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 inquire) that it was I who had failed our appointment and
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 not he. By parting with the craquemarte he \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 had further
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 salved his conscience.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Stone steps very like those I had swum from as a boy had
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 been cut into the sides of the pier. Its top was empty, nearly
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 as lush as a lawn with the grass that had rooted between its
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 stones. The ruined city, my own city o\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 f Nessus though it was
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 the Nessus of a time now long past, lay quiet before me. A
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 few birds wheeled overhead, but they-were as silent as the
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 sun-dimmed stars. Gyoll, whispering to itself in midstream,
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 already seemed detached from me and the empty hulks of
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 buildings among which I limped. As soon as I was out of sight
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 of its waters, it fell silent, like some uncertain visitor who
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 ceases to speak when we step into another room.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 It seemed that this could hardly be the quarter from which
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 (as Dorcas had told me\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 ) furniture and utensils were taken. At
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 first I looked in often at doors and windows, but nothing had
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 been left within but wrack and a^ few yellow leaves, drifted
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 already from the young trees that were overturning the paving 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 blocks. Nor did I see any sign\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2  of human pillagers, although 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 there were animal droppings and a few feathers and
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 scattered bones.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 I do not know how far inland I walked. It seemed a league,
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 though it may have been much less. Losing the transportation 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 of the Samru did not much bother m\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 e. I had walked
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 from Nessus most of the way to the mountain war, and although 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 my steps were uneven still, my bare feet had been
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 toughened on the deck. Because I had never really become
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 accustomed to carrying a sword at my waist, I drew the
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 craquemarte and\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2  put it on my shoulder, as I had often borne
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Terminus Est. The summer sunshine held that special, luxurious 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 warmth it gains when a suggestion of chill has crept
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 into the morning air. I enjoyed it, and would have enjoyed it
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 more, and the silence and solitu\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 de too, if I had not been
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 thinking of what I would say to Dorcas, if I found her, and
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 what she might say to me.
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Had I only known, I might have saved myself that concern;
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 I came upon her sooner than I could reasonably have expected, 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 and I did not speak t\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 o her\hich\f2 \emdash \loch\f2 nor did she speak to me,
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 or so far as I could judge, even see me.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 The buildings, which had been large and solid near the
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 river, had long since given way to lesser, f alien-in structures
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 that must once have been houses and shops. I do not know
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 what \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 guided me to hers. There was no sound of weeping,
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 though there may have been some small, unconscious noise,
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 the creaking of a hinge or the scrape of a shoe. Perhaps it was
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 no more than the perfume of the blossom she wore, because
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 when I saw her she had an \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 arum, freckled white and sweet as
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Dorcas herself had always been, thrust into her hair. No
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 doubt she had brought it there for that purpose, and had
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 taken out the wilted poppy and cast it down when she had
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 tied up her boat. (But I have gotten ahead of my st\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 ory.)
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 I tried to enter the building from the front, but the rotting
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 floor was falling into the foundation in places as the arches
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 under it collapsed. The storeroom at the rear was less open;
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 the silent, shadowed walk, green with ferns, had been a dangero\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 us 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 alley once, and shopkeepers had put small windows
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 there or none. Still, I found a narrow door hidden under ivy,
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 a door whose iron had been eaten like sugar by the rain,
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 whose oak was falling into mould. Stairs nearly sound led to
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 the floor above.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 She\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2  was kneeling with her back to me. She had always been
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 slender; now her shoulders made me think of a wooden chair
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 with a woman\hich\f2 \rquote \loch\f2 s jupe hung over it. Her hair, like the palest
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 gold, was the same\hich\f2 \emdash \loch\f2 unchanged since I had seen her first in
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 the Garden of Endless S\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 leep. The body of the old man who
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 had poled the skiff there lay on a bier before her, his back so
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 straight, his face, in death, so youthful, that I hardly knew
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 him. On the floor near her was a basket\hich\f2 \emdash \loch\f2 not small yet not
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 large either, and a corked water jar.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 I said nothing, and when I had watched her for a time I
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 went away. If she had been there long, I would have called to
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 her and embraced her. But she had just arrived, and I saw
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 that it was impossible. All the time I had spent in journeying
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 from Thrax to L\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 ake Diuturna, and from the lake to the war,
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 and all the time I had spent as a prisoner of Vodalus, and in
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 sailing up Gyoll, she had spent in returning here to her place,
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 where she had lived forty years ago or more though it had
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 now fallen into decay.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 As \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 I had myself, an ancient buzzing with antiquity as a
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 corpse with flies. Not that the minds of Thecla and the old
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Autarch, or the hundred contained in his, had made me old.
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 It was not their memories but my own that aged me, as I
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 thought of Dorcas shivering \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 beside me on the brown track of
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 floating sedge, both of us cold and dripping, drinking together 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 from Hildegrin's flask like two infants, which in fact
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 we had been,
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 I paid no heed to where I walked after that. I went straight
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 down a long street alive wit\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 h silence, and when it ended at
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 last. I turned at random. After a time I reached Gyoll, and
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 looking downstream saw the Samru riding at anchor at the
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 meeting place. A basilosaur swimming up from the open sea
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 would not have astounded me more.
\par 
\par \tab \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 In a few mome\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 nts I was mobbed by smiling sailors. The
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 captain wrung my hand, saying, "I was afraid we'd come too
